metadata.description:
Jeremy Shoemaker details the process of making code, docs, and tools contributions. Learn how to fork the repository, sign the Contributor License Agreement, adhere to the style guide, run tests, and get your pull requests merged.

00:00 Meet Monty 2026: Making a Pull Request to tbp.monty
00:16 Overview of Making a Code Contribution
01:20 Signing the Contributor License Agreement
01:45 Style and Type Hinting Guides
02:42 How we Triage Pull Requests
03:37 Automatic Style Checks and Tests
04:33 Benchmarks
05:22 Pull Request Review Process

This presentation is part of our December, 2025 community meetup “Meet Monty 2026: Reverse Engineering Intelligence” playlist which you can view here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXpTU6oIscrkM2ZYSohq04cudo1cGGKTb
This two-hour playlist features nine short talks from the Thousand Brains Project team explaining various aspects of the project. Learn about Monty, a new type of AI, based on the principles of the neocortex. 

Get the code: https://github.com/thousandbrainsproject/tbp.monty
Chat with our community: https://thousandbrains.discourse.group
Read the docs: https://thousandbrainsproject.readme.io
Follow us on Bluesky: https://bsky.app/profile/1000brainsproj.bsky.social
Follow us on LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/thousand-brains-project
Follow us on X: https://twitter.com/1000brainsproj
Join our meetup group: https://www.meetup.com/thousand-brains-project
Join our mailing list: https://thousandbrains.org
